[I] A small Web Browser (i.e. for handhelds)

[T] Dillo is a fast and lighteweight webbrowser.
[T]
[T] It is mainly designed for use on handhelds - but it might also be of
[T] help on old computers. It is able to render a good subset of HTML,
[T] excluding frames, JavaScript and JVM support.

[U] https://www.dillo.org/

[A] Jorge Arellano Cid <jcid@softhome.net>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/office

[E] opt libwebp

[L] GPL
